{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17492962","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17492962"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:51:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:51:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1193"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1193"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.75,0.03,0.02,0.08,0.12]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1193"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69188"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1193"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2019-11-22T06:35:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-11T11:56:35+10:30","updatedAction":"revised","acceptedAt":"2023-02-25T08:48:11+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-28 21:56:55"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1193"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"16119"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"9"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54642"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"136"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"3311"},{"type":"tags","id":"3382"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8138"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8197"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42244"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44505"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54642"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69188"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a one-day history of increasing upper abdominal pain, nausea and vomiting. He has never had these symptoms before. His medical history is unremarkable. He is a non-smoker and drinks about two standard drinks a day but did \u0027over-indulge\u0027 the night before his symptoms started. He does not take any medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination his blood pressure is 110/65 mmHg, pulse 100/min and temperature 37.2\u003Csup\u003Eo\u003C/sup\u003EC and BMI 31. There is tenderness across the upper abdomen without evidence of peritonitis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following investigations is most likely to be diagnostic?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Serum lipase","Liver function tests","Chest X-ray","Upper abdominal ultrasound","CT chest and abdomen"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s symptoms are very suggestive of acute pancreatitis, with recent excessive alcohol consumption being a well recognised risk factor. \u003Cstrong\u003ESerum lipase\u003C/strong\u003E is therefore the best diagnostic test. Levels more than three-fold the upper limit of normal within 24 hours after an acute attack would be diagnostic of acute pancreatitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn these circumstances, an \u003Cstrong\u003Eupper abdominal ultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E may be performed in the Emergency Department (ED) to help rule out acute cholecystitis, but the presence of gallstones per se does not necessarily mean acute cholecystitis and may be the aetiology of his pancreatitis. Given this patient\u0027s class I obesity, an ED ultrasound examination might not pick up the fine detail of inflammatory changes in the gallbladder wall or pancreas making it difficult to reach any diagnosis. Considering these factors, serum lipase remains the best diagnostic investigation for this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECT chest and abdomen \u003C/strong\u003Ecan be used for the evaluation of acute pancreatitis, but is not recommended as a diagnostic tool. It can provide detailed images of the abdomen and help to assess the severity of pancreatitis as well as any complications such as fluid collections or pseudocysts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver function tests \u003C/strong\u003Emay be deranged in acute gallstone pancreatitis and can be used to assess prognosis in pancreatitis but are not specific and can be abnormal in other liver and biliary diseases; therefore, they are not used as a diagnostic tool for pancreatitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChest X-ray \u003C/strong\u003Eis not indicated for the diagnosis of acute pancreas, but should be considered in circumstances where a patient\u0027s symptoms were thought to be due to a perforated viscus and remains part of the workup of any patient with an acute abdomen.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Serum lipase is the best diagnostic test for acute pancreatitis."],"references":["Gapp J, Tariq A, Chandra S. Acute Pancreatitis. [Updated 2022 Nov 4]. In: StatPearls. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2022 Jan. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482468/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54642"}},"question":{"data":{